---
title: compute_verify_cell_kzg_proof_batch_challenge (fulu-polynomial-commitments-sampling)
---
stateDiagram-v2
    direction TB

    [*] --> q_init : start
    q_init --> q_append_params : hashinput = RANDOM_CHALLENGE_KZG_CELL_BATCH_DOMAIN
    q_append_params --> q_append_lens : append FIELD_ELEMENTS_PER_BLOB, FIELD_ELEMENTS_PER_CELL
    q_append_lens --> q_hash_commitments : append len(commitments), len(cell_indices)
    q_hash_commitments --> q_hash_evals : for commitment in commitments: hashinput += commitment
    q_hash_evals --> q_append_indices : for k, coset_evals in enumerate(cosets_evals)
    q_append_indices --> q_append_evals : hashinput += commitment_indices[k], cell_indices[k]
    q_append_evals --> q_append_proof : for coset_eval: hashinput += bls_field_to_bytes(coset_eval)
    q_append_proof --> q_hash_evals : hashinput += proofs[k]
    q_hash_evals --> q_return : all k processed
    q_return --> [*] : return hash_to_bls_field(hashinput)

    note right of q_init
        INV: Fiat-Shamir heuristic: all verifier-relevant data included in hash input
        INV: Domain separator prevents cross-protocol attacks
        INV: Hash input order is deterministic and canonical
    end note
